{"id": "1414625620486258769", "channel_id": "1402538040253087766", "type": 0, "author_id": "506557286693601302", "author_name": "lykantos.", "author_bot": false, "content": "I have a question, so in Arc 2 GDoll mentions adding 21mg of 精纯银芯 which should be 'pure silver core' and I thought it's the same as the in-game currency so I looked at the EN-Morimens Term Base doc for it", "timestamp": "2025-09-08T14:57:10.397000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1414625824233226290", "channel_id": "1402538040253087766", "type": 0, "author_id": "506557286693601302", "author_name": "lykantos.", "author_bot": false, "content": "and there the item 'pure silver core' is 纯银之芯, which is technically also correct, so can I just assume it's a minor difference in phrasing?", "timestamp": "2025-09-08T14:57:58.974000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1414626103577935912", "channel_id": "1402538040253087766", "type": 0, "author_id": "506557286693601302", "author_name": "lykantos.", "author_bot": false, "content": "So I'll just tl it as Pure Silver Core (as in the in-game currency) in the story?", "timestamp": "2025-09-08T14:59:05.575000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-09-08T14:59:20.999000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1414692675684143267", "channel_id": "1402538040253087766", "type": 19, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "i think 精纯 is generally used more with regards to pure in the context of refinement/purification? whereas 纯 by itself is just pure in the sense of like, natural purity\nlike as an example (at least to me), I'd read the two as the difference between \"you can melt down soda cans to extract pure aluminum ingots\" and \"pure spring water taken from natural mountains untouched by man\"", "timestamp": "2025-09-08T19:23:37.602000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-09-08T19:29:34.778000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": ["506557286693601302"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1414625620486258769", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
